Citations
Date: 0/0/1963
Source: Packtrack to Highway
Author: CHINN
Vol / Page: 43
Edition:
Quote: After the cocksfoot was in the right condition, having been left in stooks to ripen, the seed was thrashed out of it with what was called an Irish combine. This was simply two stout sticks coupled together by a thong of bullock hide and wielded with vigour and skill by a strong man.
